Hi

I made it work with Voice Recognition


Issue: Seems like PlatformIO doesnt auto-generate srmodels (.pio/build/esp32-s3-devkitc1-n16r8) so I have to do it everytime you clean and build (after building, before flashing) (after remaking the build folder)

Answer: 
AT THIS LEVEL
PS C:\Users\mimil\OneDrive\Documents\PlatformIO\Projects\TV_Head_v1> (!! Root of your project !!)
RUN THIS
python "C:\Users\mimil\OneDrive\Documents\PlatformIO\Projects\TV_Head_v1\components\esp-sr\model\movemodel.py" `
    -d1 "C:\Users\mimil\OneDrive\Documents\PlatformIO\Projects\TV_Head_v1\sdkconfig.esp32-s3-devkitc1-n16r8" `
    -d2 "C:\Users\mimil\OneDrive\Documents\PlatformIO\Projects\TV_Head_v1\components\esp-sr" `
    -d3 "C:\Users\mimil\OneDrive\Documents\PlatformIO\Projects\TV_Head_v1\.pio\build\esp32-s3-devkitc1-n16r8"

It'll make them from movemodel.py ("d0"), referencing your sdkconfig (d1), using your esp-sr component (d2), and write them (srmodel folder with your language models) in the good folder (d3)

So basically: 
1- Do your update
2- Clean
3- Build
4- Do the python command above
5- Flash to board
6- Serial monitor (and reset board to make it start with the new code obviously)

To add voice commands: (dans le root folder, donc TV_Head_vXXX)
py -3 "C:\Users\mimil\OneDrive\Documents\PlatformIO\Projects\TV_Head_v1\components\esp-sr\tool\multinet_g2p.py" -t "Cheese;Cake;Christmas Tree, Tree; Christmas Gift, Gift; Flashbang, Think Fast Chucklenuts; Flashlight, Let there be light;Brightness normal; Brightness down; Brightness up; Brightness minimum; Brightness maximum;"
Basically on utilise l'outil g2p de multinet pour lui faire generer du phonetique qu'on met dans le sdk/menuconfig
l'exemple en haut return:
in: Cheese;Cake;Christmas Tree, Tree; Christmas Gift, Gift; Flashbang, Think Fast Chucklenuts; Flashlight, Let there be light;Brightness normal; Brightness down; Brightness up; Brightness minimum; Brightness maximum;
out: pmZ;KdK;KRgSMcS TRm,TRm;KRgSMcS GgFT,GgFT;FLasBal,vglK FaST KcKLcNcTS;FLasLiT,LfT jfR Bm LiT;BRiTNcS NeRMcL;BRiTNcS DtN;BRiTNcS cP;BRiTNcS MgNcMcM;BRiTNcS MaKScMcM;;

Note to self: If python is wrong again (3.14 instead of 3.13 for example) reinstall, update PATH, and then check the platformio.exe --version to see if Core needs to be re-installed to fit python

To upload data folder: 
pio run --target buildfs
pio run --target uploadfs